sentences: Chris O'Ryan (born July 6, 1980), known professionally as Tek, is a Grammy Award-winning Australian music producer and sound engineer.
In 1992, at the age of 12, he sang in Opera Australia's production of Hansel and Gretel.
He then studied music for two years at Box Hill College of Music in Melbourne, Australia.
In 2006, O'Ryan reunited with Tricky Stewart and over the next few years, he engineered records for Usher, Mariah Carey, Celine Dion, Rihanna, and Mary J. Blige, for which he won a Grammy Award.
